1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,490
New Tales of Gisaeng

2
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:07,500
<i>Episode 51</i>

3
00:00:07,580 --> 00:00:09,110
Soon Deok...

4
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:11,810
Yes.

5
00:00:11,820 --> 00:00:15,940
Come to our place.
Together with Director Geum.

6
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:17,440
Did Master Jeong contact you?

7
00:00:17,450 --> 00:00:19,970
It's not that, but it's important.

8
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:21,940
All right,

9
00:00:21,950 --> 00:00:24,240
If I'm to come with
Director, then the evening.

10
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:25,610
It's fine with me.

11
00:00:25,620 --> 00:00:27,450
Yes.

12
00:00:30,750 --> 00:00:33,210
Did Master Jeong contact her?

13
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:37,470
It's not that, but Hwa Ran
unnie says to come by.

14
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:40,540
Please come check this, to
see if it's done right.

15
00:00:40,550 --> 00:00:42,250
Yep.

16
00:00:55,380 --> 00:00:57,770
Yes, Madame Oh.

17
00:00:57,780 --> 00:00:59,240
Are you busy?!

18
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:01,040
No.

19
00:01:01,050 --> 00:01:04,040
Can you stop by here today?

20
00:01:04,050 --> 00:01:05,440
By myself?

21
00:01:05,450 --> 00:01:07,820
Yes, yourself for now.

22
00:01:09,020 --> 00:01:12,040
I got it. I'll come by before five.

23
00:01:12,050 --> 00:01:13,720
Okay.

24
00:01:21,450 --> 00:01:26,510
Dear, when are we going
to make winter kimchi?

25
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:30,420
We have to wait until it's cooler.
If we pickle them now, they'll get ripen too soon.

26
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:38,010
Our in-law's home... it's really so great.
Starting from the front garden, it's enormous.

27
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:40,170
Wish I could take a look around.

28
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:43,980
I'm sure they'll invite us soon.

29
00:01:44,820 --> 00:01:49,440
Dear, how do you feel?

30
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:50,670
Am I strange?

31
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,340
No.

32
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:57,350
My mind feels refreshed, and
I think it's gone for good.

33
00:01:58,250 --> 00:01:59,510
That's a relief

34
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:02,540
I should be good enough to
go to the company, right?

35
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:06,140
How many hours can you actually
work though, if you go now?

36
00:02:06,150 --> 00:02:09,140
Just go on a stroll with Andre instead.

37
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:11,210
Then you come too, Dear.

38
00:02:11,220 --> 00:02:12,140
Me too?!

39
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:14,070
Yep.

40
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:16,950
Andre, let's go.

41
00:02:19,550 --> 00:02:24,410
Um, could we go somewhere far?
Enjoy a drive too.

42
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,270
Oh, how did it go?

43
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,770
It went well.

44
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:29,970
Are all his symptoms gone?

45
00:02:29,980 --> 00:02:31,070
Yes.

46
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,610
Oh, that's good.

47
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:34,940
Please tell the madame I said thank you.

48
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:38,550
I didn't tell her it was Chairman Ah and
made it sound like it was someone else.

49
00:02:39,850 --> 00:02:41,310
I see.

50
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:43,870
Is Sa Ran okay during all this?

51
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:47,040
She was quite startled and
worried, but I think she's fine.

52
00:02:47,050 --> 00:02:49,340
Alright, then call me again
if someone else happens.

53
00:02:49,350 --> 00:02:52,020
Yes, please hang up.

54
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:58,970
I keep wanting to eat.

55
00:02:58,980 --> 00:03:01,070
Then you should be eating
a proper meal with rice.

56
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,370
Not really feel up to rice yet.

57
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:04,750
I'll run an errand and come back.

58
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:10,440
Oh, it's hot, after walking around.

59
00:03:10,450 --> 00:03:12,280
Yep.

60
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:18,120
Kid.

61
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:30,210
Now I know what true happiness is.

62
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:31,670
What is that?

63
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:35,470
Being together with family,
without any issues.

64
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,540
That's right.

65
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:40,870
Earlier, at the temple, I prayed.

66
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:44,260
That if they would pull away the
ghost, I would live diligently...

67
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:46,710
even more diligently than I have until now.

68
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:49,240
Working diligently, you mean?

69
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:53,770
Work diligently too, but put
my best into my family too.

70
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:56,570
Up until now, to be honest,
the company was priority.

71
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:58,070
Really?

72
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:00,310
Can I count on that from now on?

73
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:03,480
Wait and see. I won't change.

74
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:13,170
There will be guests coming.
Have it so that they don't look for me.

75
00:04:13,180 --> 00:04:14,650
Yes.

76
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:24,380
Yes?!

77
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:32,440
You said you'd be coming in the evening.

78
00:04:32,450 --> 00:04:35,840
I think it'll be hard for Director
to come, because of the patients.

79
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:41,120
And I was curious too.
Does it have to be both of us?

80
00:04:42,020 --> 00:04:45,610
Master Jeong...
there's nothing wrong, right?

81
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:48,620
He hasn't contacted us.

82
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:52,710
I said not to look for me. Who is it?

83
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:55,450
You have a guest here.

84
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:57,510
- Omo. -Hello!

85
00:04:57,520 --> 00:05:00,470
I thought you couldn't come.

86
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:04,510
I had a patient who was in a bad
condition, but his condition improved.

87
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,210
Do you want some tea?

88
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:07,750
I already drank a lot today.

89
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:17,250
Today is a very happy day for me.
That's why I asked to meet.

90
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:21,040
Are you getting married?

91
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:22,920
No.

92
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,550
Director will probably understand
this by looking at it.

93
00:05:29,450 --> 00:05:33,050
Genetic test result.

94
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:45,150
I'll tell you the conclusion first.
Soon Deok's daughter's been found.

95
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:48,620
You did?

96
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:51,210
Is she living well?

97
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,170
Very.

98
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:53,740
Where?!

99
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:59,040
Please don't be startled. It's actually...

100
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:01,450
It's Sa Ran

101
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,910
Sa Ran?!

102
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,910
Really?!

103
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:08,070
That's what the test result shows.

104
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,640
What did you test with?

105
00:06:09,650 --> 00:06:14,840
Blood test. Last time, you
had a nosebleed, right?

106
00:06:14,850 --> 00:06:17,520
How can it be Sa Ran?

107
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,310
It was an ahjumma who worked at
our house who took the child.

108
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:25,240
I thought it was a possibility too.
So, I asked my mother-in-law and she said no.

109
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:28,540
She said she went to check and
Sa Ran's mom isn't that ahjumma.

110
00:06:28,550 --> 00:06:30,010
Why did she go check?

111
00:06:30,020 --> 00:06:34,040
Because Sa Ran resembles my
mother-in-law so much from her youth.

112
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:36,390
It's for sure.

113
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:38,780
Sa Ran said this to me when
she was getting married...

114
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:41,210
that she was a foundling.

115
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:43,500
Her current mom is her step-mom

116
00:06:43,580 --> 00:06:46,110
and her real mom passed away
when she was in high school.

117
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,240
But she later found out that
wasn't her real mom either,

118
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:50,620
but the mom who raised her.

119
00:06:51,980 --> 00:06:53,170
How could it be?

120
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:54,790
It's probably the case that her deceased mom

121
00:06:54,850 --> 00:06:58,500
was the ahjumma who worked
at Director Geum's house.

122
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,270
Are you sure?

123
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:06,400
Last week,

124
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:10,070
after I heard the whole story from Soon
Deok, and I was about to go to sleep.

125
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,870
Sa Ran's story came to my thoughts.

126
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:17,220
For it to be just a coincidence...
the circumstances are too similar,

127
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:20,710
so even though I still had doubt...

128
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,720
I called Sa Ran to come the next day.

129
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:27,140
I said she looked like she was
indigested and I pricked her fingers.

130
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:33,150
Then, I asked Doctor Kim Woo Jin of Daekyung
Hospital to run a DNA test for blood relations.

131
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,970
The result came out today,

132
00:07:36,030 --> 00:07:38,600
and I was told it's a 99. 9% match.

133
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:41,450
Blood relations without a doubt.

134
00:07:46,950 --> 00:07:49,570
Soon, Ah Da Mo will be coming here.

135
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:51,980
I was afraid it would startle her too much.

136
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:55,540
Since she's with child, I don't
want to startle her and the fetus.

137
00:07:55,670 --> 00:07:58,240
So I called her husband to come first.

138
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:02,010
Sa Ran is?

139
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:05,520
Sa Ran is?!

140
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:09,720
But... the test couldn't be wrong...

141
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:12,310
it couldn't be wrong.

142
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:16,150
The blood from both were submitted
properly, and the result is this.

143
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:19,370
What are we to do... our Sa Ranee...

144
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:22,440
our pitiful daughter.

145
00:08:22,450 --> 00:08:25,220
Because of this foolish mom of hers...

146
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:27,870
she had to become a gisaeng too.

147
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:32,670
All the food for the
hair-raising ceremony...

148
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:36,370
I made them with these hands of mine!

149
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:38,370
How could it happened?

150
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:40,990
What do I do?

151
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:46,840
She grew up thinking they
were her real parents.

152
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:49,940
But after the remarriage, her
current step-mom told her.

153
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:53,350
And that's how she ended
up becoming a gisaeng.

154
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:58,540
The first day she came, saying
she wanted to become a gisaeng.

155
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:02,140
The girl came in a daze.

156
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:04,610
Her wounds appeared to be so grave to me.

157
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:08,380
So I sent her away, telling
her to reconsider.

158
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:13,570
Da Mo... is he coming here without knowing?

159
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:14,970
Yes,

160
00:09:14,980 --> 00:09:17,310
He said he'd be here by five.

161
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,540
She went through that kind of neglect...

162
00:09:19,630 --> 00:09:22,540
that kind of pain.

163
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:26,010
Regardless, the end result is good.

164
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:30,110
How can I face Sa Ran now? With what right?

165
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:34,910
I asked her last time, and she said she was trying
hard to force herself not to think about it.

166
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:38,180
Since she didn't have a
way to find her parents.

167
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:42,940
Think of it as fate.

168
00:09:43,070 --> 00:09:47,670
Regardless of what...
you've found her now, so it's good now.

169
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,820
A good thing for you both.

170
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:56,050
Omo, she's bleeding again.

171
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:02,880
She needs to lay down and stabilize a bit.

172
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,970
Go to the room next door and lay down.

173
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:06,870
I want to see her now.

174
00:10:06,930 --> 00:10:09,270
After Da Mo gets here,
we'll discuss with him.

175
00:10:09,330 --> 00:10:10,580
Get ahold of yourself.

176
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:13,410
I'm all right, I am all right.

177
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:16,220
Here.

178
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,710
Hello.

179
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:43,500
Have you been well?

180
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:46,770
I heard you'll be a dad next year.

181
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:47,840
Who said that?

182
00:10:47,930 --> 00:10:50,480
Please go in

183
00:10:52,690 --> 00:10:55,250
Did something unpleasant happen?

184
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:58,790
I've shed some rare tears.

185
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:02,870
I think we need to go.
Her nosebleeding won't stop.

186
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,350
You came.

187
00:11:04,450 --> 00:11:07,620
Oh, you're!...

188
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,670
I'll call you later.

189
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:11,600
Yes.

190
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:18,810
Did he come with Kitchen Head?

191
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:20,810
Yep,

192
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,470
I think you'll need to
change how you address them.

193
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,970
And I will lower my speech
to you too, from now on.

194
00:11:25,980 --> 00:11:27,340
Yes,

195
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:31,440
I should be calling her Madame, but I've
gotten too used to calling her Kitchen Head.

196
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:34,980
Not Kitchen Head, and not Madame either.

197
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:38,660
Actually, she's your mother-in-law.

198
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:45,300
Since Han Soon Deok and Director
Geum are Sa Ran's real parents.

199
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:51,570
You also knew, Chief Madame?

200
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:54,470
That Sa Ran was left outside Ra Ra's house?

201
00:11:54,620 --> 00:11:56,570
You already knew?

202
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:57,490
Yes.

203
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,710
How?

204
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:03,170
Father-in-law knew which house they took Sa
Ran from, all these years, as it turns out.

205
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:06,710
Even though, previously he said he didn't know,
when I had my sister-in-law ask him about it.

206
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:11,440
I followed the address he gave and went to see
the house, and it was actually Ra Ra's house.

207
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:12,530
Director Geum's house.

208
00:12:12,630 --> 00:12:13,950
But then?

209
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,010
Then, you should've revealed the truth.

210
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:18,070
Sa Ran didn't want that.

211
00:12:18,170 --> 00:12:21,940
She said it would make her feel too
wretched and awkward to her friend.

212
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:24,260
On the off-chance that it's true,

213
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:27,020
I went behind Sa Ran's back
and hired an acting ahjumma.

214
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,080
But then?

215
00:12:28,170 --> 00:12:29,600
They told her no one came
to look for the foundling.

216
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:31,640
Came to look for the child?

217
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:32,270
Yes.

218
00:12:32,350 --> 00:12:34,970
Who said that?
Who said no one looked for it?

219
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:39,530
Since she said it was a middle-aged
madame, it must have been Kitchen Head.

220
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:41,690
It's somebody else.

221
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,710
It might be Ra Ra's real mother

222
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,620
Did you hear this from my mother-in-law?

223
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:47,040
Gong Joo's mother?!

224
00:12:47,050 --> 00:12:49,160
Yes.

225
00:12:49,850 --> 00:12:52,290
Han Soon Deok and...

226
00:12:52,350 --> 00:12:55,790
Sa Ran's genetic test... I applied for it.

227
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,730
And today it came out as them being
biologically mother and daughter.

228
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:03,870
How could that be?

229
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:06,450
Director Geum knew Han Soon
Deok before he was married,

230
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,750
and that's when Sa Ran was conceived.

231
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:11,540
For many reasons, Soon Deok found
herself unsuitable for him,

232
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:14,090
so she didn't go meet him as promised.

233
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:17,800
And a few months later is when
she found out she was pregnant.

234
00:13:17,810 --> 00:13:20,820
When Director Geum met with the woman
the families matched together,

235
00:13:20,830 --> 00:13:24,120
he married Ra Ra's mother.

236
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:25,880
So what could she do?

237
00:13:25,890 --> 00:13:29,690
She had the baby and left
it outside the Geum's.

238
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,320
But he sent his own child
away to a stranger?

239
00:13:32,330 --> 00:13:34,500
Without knowing.

240
00:13:34,510 --> 00:13:36,680
Soon Deok, she...

241
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:38,620
She's too innocent, like her name says.

242
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:42,360
She thought he would know and didn't say
it was his daughter on a piece of paper.

243
00:13:44,530 --> 00:13:46,910
That family never imagined
it was their bloodline.

244
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:50,050
And, the deceased grandfather
said they wouldn't raise her.

245
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:51,910
Why?

246
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:55,120
Because his second daughter-in-law
was about to give birth very soon.

247
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:59,520
And that's how the ahjumma who worked there
ended up taking Sa Ran away to raise.

248
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:02,360
This is all really true?

249
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:04,220
The fact that Soon Deok had a baby...

250
00:14:04,230 --> 00:14:07,240
she only told me that last week.

251
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:09,920
The part about the child taken
by the working ahjumma.

252
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:12,210
Concurred with Sa Ran's story.

253
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:14,160
And that's why I submitted
a test to be done.

254
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:15,360
With what?

255
00:14:15,370 --> 00:14:16,900
Soon Deok...

256
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:20,520
she was so upset that day,
she had a nosebleed.

257
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:21,650
So, with that,

258
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:25,020
and with the blood from pricks I did on
