wanted to do a DNA test.

788
00:50:47,330 --> 00:50:49,790
He did?

789
00:50:50,470 --> 00:50:53,560
Saying she clearly seemed
like our offspring.

790
00:50:53,970 --> 00:50:57,340
But I stopped him and told him no.

791
00:50:57,440 --> 00:51:01,280
How could I have imagined it?

792
00:51:05,930 --> 00:51:07,330
Hair.

793
00:51:07,420 --> 00:51:08,820
Your head hurts?

794
00:51:08,900 --> 00:51:11,840
Which one should I give you?

795
00:51:12,130 --> 00:51:14,040
Grandfather.

796
00:51:25,580 --> 00:51:29,080
That day, he...

797
00:51:30,470 --> 00:51:32,990
as he was passing away.

798
00:51:33,070 --> 00:51:36,720
He put his hand out saying "hair"...

799
00:51:36,820 --> 00:51:43,690
I thought he meant his head was aching, so I
was trying to give him the pill envelope.

800
00:51:59,090 --> 00:52:03,280
Today, I spent some money
to keep up an appearance.

801
00:52:03,290 --> 00:52:04,740
What appearance money?

802
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:08,940
The broads told me I should buy
since I have a rich son-in-law now.

803
00:52:09,070 --> 00:52:10,940
So I couldn't just behave
as if I was poor either.

804
00:52:10,950 --> 00:52:15,810
They say if a person starts to think they are
poor, then, they really will become poor.

805
00:52:15,820 --> 00:52:17,440
You did great!

806
00:52:17,530 --> 00:52:21,640
When we were little, the moms would squeeze
our noses to let the snots out, right?

807
00:52:21,790 --> 00:52:25,920
That was meant for us to live big.

808
00:52:26,450 --> 00:52:27,220
Really?

809
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:29,110
Yes.

810
00:52:29,120 --> 00:52:31,240
I'm out right now.

811
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:32,820
Yes.

812
00:52:33,620 --> 00:52:36,710
When I said I broke up with Da Mo ssi.

813
00:52:37,130 --> 00:52:40,310
She told me to go be a gisaeng.

814
00:52:40,410 --> 00:52:44,280
I said no, and she began to torment me.

815
00:52:44,440 --> 00:52:49,340
She knew I drank milk every morning,
but she would empty the cartons.

816
00:52:49,350 --> 00:52:50,560
Why, that...

817
00:52:50,630 --> 00:52:53,940
And put only my shoes out in the
balcony where sun comes in.

818
00:52:53,950 --> 00:52:56,050
My world...

819
00:52:57,550 --> 00:53:00,730
It was quite difficult.

820
00:53:01,580 --> 00:53:04,480
But I still endured through.

821
00:53:05,330 --> 00:53:08,010
So one day, she...

822
00:53:08,170 --> 00:53:10,170
Told me about that.

823
00:53:10,280 --> 00:53:12,180
That you were a foundling?

824
00:53:12,310 --> 00:53:15,840
Since they fed and educated me...

825
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:18,410
If the marriage is a dead issue...

826
00:53:18,540 --> 00:53:22,370
It's my duty to, at least,
earn money to pay them back.

827
00:53:24,550 --> 00:53:28,980
Oh my, and her face didn't look so evil.

828
00:53:28,990 --> 00:53:31,270
It's all my fault.

829
00:53:31,380 --> 00:53:33,750
Because I was so pathetic.

830
00:53:33,880 --> 00:53:37,210
I couldn't tell anyone about it.

831
00:53:37,460 --> 00:53:39,970
And this is my first time mentioning it.

832
00:53:40,030 --> 00:53:42,400
What else?

833
00:53:42,720 --> 00:53:45,070
Now that I've talked about it.

834
00:53:45,230 --> 00:53:47,240
I feel a bit less burdened.

835
00:53:47,330 --> 00:53:50,140
How broken-hearted you must have felt.

836
00:53:50,890 --> 00:53:53,230
To go through that...

837
00:53:54,730 --> 00:53:57,020
It's all in the past.

838
00:53:57,110 --> 00:54:02,620
Regardless, I entered Buyonggak and
that led to marrying Da Mo ssi.

839
00:54:03,500 --> 00:54:07,080
And thanks to Madame Oh, we meet like this.

840
00:54:08,550 --> 00:54:10,340
I don't want to resent you.

841
00:54:10,450 --> 00:54:13,820
You should resent.

842
00:54:15,090 --> 00:54:17,180
I feel so happy.

843
00:54:17,190 --> 00:54:19,740
And thankful.

844
00:54:20,820 --> 00:54:23,220
How did you ever...

845
00:54:23,990 --> 00:54:27,390
How did our daughter get
to grow up so beautifully.

846
00:54:47,790 --> 00:54:50,060
Who is it?

847
00:54:51,450 --> 00:54:54,890
Oh, our daughter... without calling first?

848
00:54:54,970 --> 00:54:57,080
What happened to son-in-law Geum?

849
00:54:57,160 --> 00:54:59,240
He didn't come.

850
00:54:59,350 --> 00:55:01,140
Did you and Ja fight?

851
00:55:01,150 --> 00:55:03,140
No.

852
00:55:05,190 --> 00:55:08,180
Unnie found her real parents.

853
00:55:08,380 --> 00:55:09,620
Sa Ran did?

854
00:55:09,700 --> 00:55:10,740
How?

855
00:55:10,750 --> 00:55:14,010
It's none other than Ja's uncle and aunt.

856
00:55:14,100 --> 00:55:18,530
Uncle and aunt... then Ra Ra's?

857
00:55:18,630 --> 00:55:20,090
Yes.

858
00:55:20,460 --> 00:55:24,240
So this means Unnie walked down the aisle
holding her real dad's hand, at her wedding.

859
00:55:24,440 --> 00:55:28,140
You little brat. What joke is this?

860
00:55:28,150 --> 00:55:31,380
Then call Unnie and see if it's a joke.

861
00:55:31,390 --> 00:55:35,720
Ra Ra unnie said they
even did a DNA test too.

862
00:55:38,390 --> 00:55:39,910
Mom, what are you going to do now?

863
00:55:39,990 --> 00:55:40,940
What?

864
00:55:41,040 --> 00:55:44,190
About forcing her to become a gisaeng?

865
00:55:49,790 --> 00:55:51,320
What are you doing?

866
00:55:51,440 --> 00:55:53,550
I'm playing with Andre.

867
00:55:53,610 --> 00:55:56,390
Don't you want to see some Grand
Prince, since it's been a long time?

868
00:55:56,510 --> 00:55:58,240
Shark fin, you mean?

869
00:55:58,320 --> 00:55:59,710
Yes.

870
00:55:59,810 --> 00:56:01,590
Come out with Sa Ran to Beijing House.

871
00:56:01,710 --> 00:56:03,880
Sa Ran went out and isn't home.

872
00:56:04,010 --> 00:56:05,680
But she's with child. Where?

873
00:56:05,690 --> 00:56:08,640
Da Mo came home during the
day and took her out.

874
00:56:08,760 --> 00:56:10,740
Did they go to the hospital or something?

875
00:56:10,820 --> 00:56:12,750
Nothing like that.

876
00:56:12,830 --> 00:56:14,980
I suppose they have some
business to tend to.

877
00:56:14,990 --> 00:56:17,380
What business to tend to,
during his work hour?

878
00:56:17,460 --> 00:56:19,980
Just bat an eye.

879
00:56:20,060 --> 00:56:22,050
I'm sure they'll tell us later.

880
00:56:22,170 --> 00:56:25,030
You should receive our greeting.

881
00:56:26,780 --> 00:56:28,300
On what right?

882
00:56:28,400 --> 00:56:31,390
It wasn't your choice either.

883
00:56:32,320 --> 00:56:34,960
Do that.

884
00:56:37,720 --> 00:56:41,250
Is this a dream or is this reality?

885
00:56:42,990 --> 00:56:46,510
Do one for Grandpa too, though
it's not his memorial day.

886
00:56:46,700 --> 00:56:48,690
Yes.

887
00:57:03,650 --> 00:57:07,680
If he were alive, how happy would he be.

888
00:57:07,800 --> 00:57:11,850
As you know, I made a lot of mistakes.

889
00:57:12,050 --> 00:57:14,630
Please forgive me and accept me fondly.

890
00:57:14,750 --> 00:57:16,140
I will do well in the future.

891
00:57:16,220 --> 00:57:19,550
We share the same sentiment.

892
00:57:33,420 --> 00:57:36,510
They should actually be grateful to us.

893
00:57:36,520 --> 00:57:37,280
Grateful for what?

894
00:57:37,290 --> 00:57:41,080
For raising her. And putting her through school.
And feeding her. And clothing her.

895
00:57:41,090 --> 00:57:43,240
Did you feed and clothe her?
And educate her?

896
00:57:43,250 --> 00:57:46,160
Spouses are two hearts in one body, girl.

897
00:57:46,240 --> 00:57:48,240
If your father did, then we did it together.

898
00:57:48,320 --> 00:57:50,020
Then you shouldn't have made her a gisaeng.

899
00:57:50,070 --> 00:57:51,170
Why are you nitpicking about it?

900
00:57:51,280 --> 00:57:53,150
Because I feel shameful to face them.

901
00:57:53,240 --> 00:57:55,160
No need to feel ashamed.

902
00:57:55,220 --> 00:57:58,360
We're not the one who kicked
out our own bloodline.

903
00:57:58,440 --> 00:58:03,480
All we ever did was a great deed, of raising
her like she was our own child, you know.

904
00:58:05,740 --> 00:58:08,270
Don't you sigh.

905
00:58:09,190 --> 00:58:10,350
I'll eat it well.

906
00:58:10,450 --> 00:58:12,080
Yes. Yes.

907
00:58:12,210 --> 00:58:14,280
I'm not in any mind to cook.

908
00:58:14,390 --> 00:58:15,710
Oh, of course.

909
00:58:15,810 --> 00:58:18,640
Next time, I'll make you
something delicious.

910
00:58:18,650 --> 00:58:21,520
Is this a dream or is this reality?

911
00:58:21,620 --> 00:58:24,320
That's what I want to say.

912
00:58:30,050 --> 00:58:32,340
Would that be enough, eating like that?

913
00:58:32,350 --> 00:58:33,210
Yes.

914
00:58:33,220 --> 00:58:34,840
I can only eat things that are refreshing.

915
00:58:34,850 --> 00:58:38,140
This is your first meal
at your parent's house.

916
00:58:38,220 --> 00:58:40,410
Will it do that you're only
eating rice and cucumbers?

917
00:58:40,420 --> 00:58:41,780
It's yummy.

918
00:58:41,850 --> 00:58:42,940
You don't have ice cream, do you?

919
00:58:42,950 --> 00:58:43,810
We do.

920
00:58:43,820 --> 00:58:46,540
Your mother-in-law likes walnut ice cream.

921
00:58:46,550 --> 00:58:47,880
Really?

922
00:58:47,890 --> 00:58:51,580
Sa Ran's been living on ice cream
and sweet bean porridge these days.

923
00:58:51,590 --> 00:58:54,520
You two mother and daughter are alike.

924
00:58:57,270 --> 00:58:59,920
The issue is with son-in-law Ah's.

925
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:01,840
Would they treat us like in-laws now?

926
00:59:01,850 --> 00:59:04,240
They won't even look at us.

927
00:59:04,470 --> 00:59:07,680
They'll just be chummy with Ra Ra's.

928
00:59:07,690 --> 00:59:08,510
Aren't you hungry?

929
00:59:08,520 --> 00:59:11,470
You're hungry under the situation now?

930
00:59:12,350 --> 00:59:14,970
These kids... not even calling.

931
00:59:15,470 --> 00:59:18,880
Just leave them be.
So they can enjoy a date.

932
00:59:18,890 --> 00:59:20,460
Yesterday, we did.

933
00:59:20,540 --> 00:59:23,550
The house feels like a temple building.

934
00:59:23,630 --> 00:59:26,170
But we have Andre.

935
00:59:26,270 --> 00:59:29,290
Andre is just Andre.

936
00:59:29,570 --> 00:59:34,080
Are you really fine?

937
00:59:34,230 --> 00:59:36,960
If you ever sense that I'm
strange, even a little,

938
00:59:37,060 --> 00:59:39,020
tell me right away.

939
00:59:39,170 --> 00:59:40,760
Yes.

940
00:59:43,520 --> 00:59:45,400
Do you remember the fortune cookie?

941
00:59:45,480 --> 00:59:46,480
Yes.

942
00:59:46,580 --> 00:59:50,800
It was accurate exactly on that day.
To have a happy day with your child.

943
00:59:50,990 --> 00:59:52,310
It was, indeed.

944
00:59:52,320 --> 00:59:54,980
And Master Jeong was so
accurate like a ghost too.

945
00:59:55,070 --> 00:59:57,840
He said if you marry, you
will find your child.

946
00:59:57,850 --> 01:00:00,580
That's why they rushed to marry.

947
01:00:00,760 --> 01:00:02,310
I can't believe this.

948
01:00:02,320 --> 01:00:05,250
Want me to pinch you?

949
01:00:06,920 --> 01:00:11,520
But Mother-in-law, you are so young, you
must feel wronged to be called "grandma"...

950
01:00:11,570 --> 01:00:12,450
No

951
01:00:12,550 --> 01:00:13,810
I am so happy.

952
01:00:13,910 --> 01:00:16,110
And joyful beyond words can express.

953
01:00:16,120 --> 01:00:17,210
What about you, Father-in-law?

954
01:00:17,220 --> 01:00:19,780
I am the same, of course.

955
01:00:19,970 --> 01:00:23,680
Did you, by chance, have a
conception dream of me?

956
01:00:23,770 --> 01:00:24,810
Of course.

957
01:00:24,930 --> 01:00:27,890
My... she still doubts?

958
01:00:27,990 --> 01:00:30,840
Didn't she even dream your
conception dream for you?

959
01:00:30,850 --> 01:00:32,010
Yes.

960
01:00:32,090 --> 01:00:37,880
The sky had a very full moon so I was
looking at it completely enraptured.

961
01:00:38,040 --> 01:00:43,360
And in just a little bit, from that big moon,
small moons were popping out like popcorn.

962
01:00:43,740 --> 01:00:47,420
They all popped out and fell into my skirt.

963
01:00:47,500 --> 01:00:49,280
It's a great dream.

964
01:00:49,290 --> 01:00:50,600
Of course.

965
01:00:50,690 --> 01:00:53,580
It's a dream that means the
child will live well in luxury.

966
01:00:53,700 --> 01:00:56,280
Your mom barely hung on
in life, with that dream.

967
01:00:56,440 --> 01:00:58,980
Because she had such a sturdy dream.

968
01:00:59,110 --> 01:01:01,760
And now all the dregs are gone.

969
01:01:02,740 --> 01:01:05,230
A beautiful Sa Ran like you...

970
01:01:05,310 --> 01:01:06,410
is my daughter.

971
01:01:06,420 --> 01:01:10,200
Not just beautiful.
She's so good-hearted as well.

972
01:01:16,800 --> 01:01:18,730
It's father.

973
01:01:19,350 --> 01:01:20,600
Hello?

974
01:01:20,680 --> 01:01:22,200
Why aren't you guys coming home?

975
01:01:22,270 --> 01:01:23,560
We're about to leave.

976
01:01:23,660 --> 01:01:25,260
Where are you?

977
01:01:25,370 --> 01:01:26,940
I'll tell you after I get home.

978
01:01:27,090 --> 01:01:29,320
You sure it's not because Sa Ran is ill?

979
01:01:29,380 --> 01:01:31,000
It's not.

980
01:01:31,130 --> 01:01:32,080
Alright.

981
01:01:32,210 --> 01:01:34,430
Yes.

982
01:01:34,860 --> 01:01:37,880
Tell your father I'd like to meet him first.

983
01:01:37,950 --> 01:01:38,950
When would be good?

984
01:01:39,010 --> 01:01:41,580
Tomorrow works too.

985
01:01:41,680 --> 01:01:43,680
So, anytime that works with
your father's schedule.

986
01:01:43,800 --> 01:01:45,550
Yes.

987
01:01:48,890 --> 01:01:52,240
I wish I could talk to you
throughout the night.

988
01:01:52,390 --> 01:01:54,340
I'll come again tomorrow, Grandma.

989
01:01:54,400 --> 01:01:56,280
Alright.

990
01:02:06,410 --> 01:02:08,580
Sa Ran.

991
01:02:08,680 --> 01:02:10,990
You should live with us too.

992
01:02:11,100 --> 01:02:12,380
Of course.

993
01:02:12,390 --> 01:02:13,810
Yes.

994
01:02:13,910 --> 01:02:14,940
What about me?

995
01:02:15,060 --> 01:02:18,330
The thread won't follow the needle?

996
01:02:21,220 --> 01:02:23,970
What expression do you suppose
my father would have?

997
01:02:29,730 --> 01:02:31,560
It's all done.

998
01:02:31,620 --> 01:02:34,750
Yes. I was going to wash my hands.

999
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:37,240
You haven't heard, right?

1000
01:02:37,360 --> 01:02:38,300
About what?

1001
01:02:38,380 --> 01:02:42,380
Miss Dan is Kitchen Head Han
Soon Deok's real daughter.

1002
01:02:42,530 --> 01:02:43,320
What?!

1003
01:02:43,420 --> 01:02:46,160
And the real dad is Director Geum.

1004
01:02:46,340 --> 01:02:49,500
So you mean, Eun Sung's
daughter-in-law, Dan Sa Ran is...?

1005
01:02:49,570 --> 01:02:50,960
Yes.

1006
01:02:51,220 --> 01:02:52,820
Oh my world.

1007
01:02:56,040 --> 01:02:59,050
Manager. Manager!

1008
01:03:03,500 --> 01:03:06,080
Where did you guys go for the whole day?

1009
01:03:06,210 --> 01:03:07,690
It wasn't a whole day.

1010
01:03:07,820 --> 01:03:09,420
Maybe you went to the villa?

1011
01:03:09,500 --> 01:03:10,470
To see the fallen leaves?

1012
01:03:10,530 --> 01:03:12,300
No.

1013
01:03:12,980 --> 01:03:15,000
Father...

1014
01:03:15,060 --> 01:03:19,280
Sa Ran found her real parents who bore her.

1015
01:03:19,490 --> 01:03:21,620
What?!

1016
01:03:22,360 --> 01:03:23,660
How?!

1017
01:03:23,750 --> 01:03:24,660
Through blood test.

1018
01:03:24,740 --> 01:03:26,770
Where do they live? In Seoul?

1019
01:03:26,870 --> 01:03:27,440
Yes.

1020
01:03:27,510 --> 01:03:29,340
We went to see them and had dinner.

1021
01:03:29,440 --> 01:03:30,630
They called you?

1022
01:03:30,740 --> 01:03:33,440
We only found out yesterday, but...

1023
01:03:33,450 --> 01:03:36,570
Father, don't be startled.

1024
01:03:37,040 --> 01:03:42,250
Those two who were seated at Sa Ran's
presiding seats, at the wedding.

1025
01:03:42,930 --> 01:03:46,430
Those two who sat at the
presiding seats were...

1026
01:03:47,180 --> 01:03:49,030
Hospital director Geum Eo San?

1027
01:03:49,130 --> 01:03:50,840
Yes!